      "side": 1,
      "message": "This new AST node isn\u0027t handled by the formatter, so `cue fmt` silently destroys tagged interpolations. With a module at language version v0.18.0:\n\n    @experiment(stringtag)\n    package m\n    a: foo \"hi \\(x)\"\n    x: \"there\"\n\n`cue fmt` rewrites it to:\n\n    a: /* unknown expr */\n    x: \"there\"\n\nThis seems like a hard blocker; we shouldn\u0027t ship new syntax in the parser unless we support it in the formatter too. this should work for both CUE_EXPERIMENT\u003dformatv2 and CUE_EXPERIMENT\u003dformatv2\u003d0, i.e. both the old and new formatters.",
      "revId": "fb5fcb933393941316c1b5c8b7dc47d59ed548fb",
