      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unlike the INTERPOLATION branch below (which calls p.parseInterpolation, wrapping the node in openComments/closeNode), this STRING branch hand-builds the *ast.Interpolation and BasicLit without any comment handling. Comments attached to a plain-string tagged literal (e.g. a trailing line comment on the string) will be dropped. Minor, but worth aligning with parseInterpolation\u0027s comment attachment.",
